Usage: createPhysicalPin [-help] <pinName> [-allowOutsideBoundary]
                         [-net <netName>] [-samePort] { { {-layer <layerName> } {-rect {x1 y1 x2 y2} | -polygon {x1 y1 x2 y2 ... xn yn}} } }

-help                                # Prints out the command usage
<pinName>                            # physical pin name (string, required)
-allowOutsideBoundary                # Do not check whether specified rect
                                     # inside design boundary (bool, optional)
-layer <layerName>                   # specify layer which the pin is specified
                                     # (string, optional)
-net <netName>                       # create physical pins on specific net
                                     # (string, optional)
-polygon {x1 y1 x2 y2 ... xn yn}     # specify the coordination of each vertex
                                     # of the shape (point_list, optional)
-rect {x1 y1 x2 y2}                  # specify the llx, lly, urx, ury
                                     # coordinates of the rect shape
                                     # (box, optional)
-samePort                            # create pin shapes on same port
                                     # (bool, optional)